  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (8d8bc28 2022-09-26T17:49:28.998299391Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen running anvil in docker (foundry:latest) we see that RPC cache is not created and not being used for other forks created on the same docker.\r\nFrom looking at the file system - the path `~/.foundry/cache/rpc/` doesn't exit\r\n\r\nthe command we are running:\r\n`anvil -f https://eth-mainnet.alchemyapi.io/v2/xxxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx-xxx_xxxxxx_xx --fork-block-number 15811946`\r\n\r\n",
